# 📄 PRD: Quiz Game App (French – Real-Time – Event Based)

## 🎯 Goal

Build a real-time quiz game app for a live event with **two teams (Red & Blue)**. The system runs entirely in the browser across 4 synced screens:

1. Projector (big screen)
2. Presenter control panel
3. Red team screen
4. Blue team screen

All screens must stay in sync via **Supabase Realtime Channels**. No database schema or permanent storage is required. State is broadcast live and transient.

---

## 🧠 Core Architecture

- **Realtime only:** use `supabase.channel().broadcast()` for all state updates.
- **Shared channel:** `quiz_channel`
- **State shape to broadcast:**

```ts
{
  questionNumber: number;
  redPoints: number;
  bluePoints: number;
  buzzerTeam: 'red' | 'blue' | null;
}
```

## Questions

- All quiz questions will be statically defined in a local file:
questions.ts

- This file will export a list of questions like:

```ts

export export const questions = [
    {
      number: 1,
      text: 'Quelle est la capitale de la France ?',
      answer: 'Paris',
      points: 10,
      penalty: -5,
    },
    {
      number: 2,
      text: 'Combien y a-t-il de continents sur Terre ?',
      answer: '7',
      points: 10,
      penalty: -3,
    },
  // ...
];
```

- All screens should import from this file and render based on questionNumber


## Screens & Functional Requirements
1. Projector Screen (/projector)
- Display both team scores (very large)
- Display current question number and text (from questions.ts)
- Highlight team that buzzed first
- If game hasn't started: show "En attente..." centered

2. Presenter Screen (/presenter)
- Controls:
    - Increment/decrement red/blue points
    - Set buzzerTeam to "red" or "blue"
    - Advance questionNumber
    - Reset buzzerTeam
- Every action broadcasts new full state to the channel

3. Team Screens (/team/red and /team/blue)
- Display:
    - Team score
    - Large "Buzz!" button

- On press:
    - If buzzerTeam is null, update buzzerTeam with this team’s color
    - Otherwise: disable button (already buzzed)

## 🌐 Realtime Behavior
- Every screen listens to updates on quiz_channel
- Presenter emits full updated state as the source of truth

- UI across all clients updates reactively on each state broadcast